<div id=3D"outline-container-org63a17cd" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"org63a17cd">Relocatable Compiler</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-org63a17cd">
<p>
A compiler installation can now be moved or copied with no risk
of hard-to-debug errors due to mixing incompatible bytecode runtime interpr=
eters.
</p>

<p>
In practice, this means that creating a local switch when there is a
global switch with the same compiler version and configuration
available can be done by cloning the global switch rather than
recompiling the whole compiler.
</p>

<p>
This should considerably reduce the time required to create
new local opam switches out-of-the-box.
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-org3b1e111" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"org3b1e111">Polymorphic Functions as Function Arguments</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-org3b1e111">
<p>
Higher-rank polymorphic functions can now be defined directly by
using an explicit type annotation in a function argument
</p>

<div class=3D"org-src-container">
<pre class=3D"src src-ocaml"><code><span style=3D"color: #242521; font-weig=
ht: bold;">let</span> <span style=3D"color: #a7601f;">apply_map</span> (<sp=
an style=3D"color: #007a9f;">map</span>:<span style=3D"color: #444fcf; font=
-weight: bold;"> 'a 'b. ('a -&gt; 'b) -&gt; 'a list -&gt; 'b list</span>) =
=3D
  map string_of_int [1;2;3], map <span style=3D"color: #557400; font-weight=
: bold;">List.</span>singleton [<span style=3D"color: #ca3400;">"x"</span>;=
 <span style=3D"color: #ca3400;">"y"</span>]
<span style=3D"color: #242521; font-weight: bold;">let</span> <span style=
=3D"color: #007a9f;">_</span> =3D apply_map <span style=3D"color: #557400; =
font-weight: bold;">List.</span>map
</code></pre>
</div>

<p>
Previously defining such a function required going through either a record =
or an object
with a polymorphic field or methods
</p>

<div class=3D"org-src-container">
<pre class=3D"src src-ocaml"><code><span style=3D"color: #242521; font-weig=
ht: bold;">type</span> <span style=3D"color: #444fcf; font-weight: bold;">m=
ap</span> =3D { map: 'a 'b. ('a -&gt; 'b) -&gt; 'a list -&gt; 'b list }
<span style=3D"color: #242521; font-weight: bold;">let</span> <span style=
=3D"color: #a7601f;">apply_map</span> {<span style=3D"color: #007a9f;">map<=
/span>} =3D
  map string_of_int [1;2;3], map <span style=3D"color: #557400; font-weight=
: bold;">List.</span>singleton [<span style=3D"color: #ca3400;">"x"</span>;=
 <span style=3D"color: #ca3400;">"y"</span>]
</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-orgb0d6f1f" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"orgb0d6f1f">Search and Replace Substring Functions</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-orgb0d6f1f">
<p>
The <code>String</code> module has been extended with many functions
for searching and replacing substrings inside a string.
</p>

<div class=3D"org-src-container">
<pre class=3D"src src-ocaml"><code><span style=3D"color: #242521; font-weig=
ht: bold;">let</span> <span style=3D"color: #007a9f;">_true</span> =3D <spa=
n style=3D"color: #557400; font-weight: bold;">String.</span>includes <span=
 style=3D"color: #444fcf; font-weight: bold;">~affix</span>:<span style=3D"=
color: #ca3400;">"aba"</span> <span style=3D"color: #ca3400;">"abbaba"</spa=
n>
<span style=3D"color: #242521; font-weight: bold;">let</span> <span style=
=3D"color: #007a9f;">sentence</span> =3D <span style=3D"color: #557400; fon=
t-weight: bold;">String.</span>replace_all <span style=3D"color: #444fcf; f=
ont-weight: bold;">~sub</span>:<span style=3D"color: #ca3400;">"&#119101;"<=
/span> <span style=3D"color: #444fcf; font-weight: bold;">~by</span>:<span =
style=3D"color: #ca3400;">"word"</span> <span style=3D"color: #ca3400;">"A =
&#119101; is re&#119101;ed"</span>
</code></pre>
</div>

<p>
The substring search is using the 2-way string matching algorithm
which has the advantage of requiring constant space memory overhead
independently of the needle size.
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-org28d4349" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"org28d4349">Generalised Local Definitions</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-org28d4349">
<p>
It is now always possible to define locally a type,
a class, a module type or any kind of item that can be defined
globally:
