<div id=3D"outline-container-org5e643ba" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"org5e643ba">GC improvements</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-org5e643ba">
<p>
Some of the ongoing work to improve the pacing of the garbage
collector has been integrated in OCaml 5.5.0, two of the important
changes in OCaml 5.5 GC are
</p>

<ul class=3D"org-ul">
<li>the addition of a sweep-only phase at the start of major GC</li>
<li>the addition of an idle phase to smooth the behaviour of the GC
at the start.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-org1d734c0" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"org1d734c0">Many incremental changes</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-org1d734c0">
<ul class=3D"org-ul">
<li>The Windows implementation is no more reliant on Winpthreads</li>
<li>Around 60 new standard library functions</li>
<li>Around 90 various improvements</li>
<li>A dozen of documentation updates</li>
<li>Around 40 bug fixes</li>
</ul>

<p>
Please report any unexpected behaviours on the <a href=3D"https://github.co=
m/ocaml/ocaml/issues">OCaml issue
tracker</a> and post any questions or
comments you might have on our <a href=3D"https://discuss.ocaml.org">discus=
sion forums</a>.
</p>

<p>
The full list of changes can be found in the full changelog.
</p>

<p>
Happy hacking,
Florian Angeletti for the OCaml team.
</p>

<p>
&mdash;
</p>
</div>
